1984年，《新闻周刊》的记者Steven Levy出版了历史上第一本介绍Hanckers的著作-

《黑客：计算机革命的英雄》	(Hanckers:Heroes of the computer Revolution)

黑客的价值观六条 "黑客伦理"    (Hanckers Ethic)

One:
Access to computer-and anything that might teach you something about 

the way the word works-should be unlimited and total.

Always yield to the Hands-On Imperative!


Two:
All information should be free


Three:
Mistrust Authority-Promote Decentralization


Four:
Hackers should be judged by their hacking,

not bogus ariteria such as,

degrees, age, race, orposition.


Five:
You can create art beauty on a compuer


Six:
Computers can change your life for the better.





"对于黑客来说，关着的门就是一种挑衅，

而锁着的门则是一种侮辱......

黑客相信，只要有助于改变现状、探索未知，

人们就应该被允许自由的使用各种工具和信息.

当一个黑客需要一样东西帮助自己进行创造

进行探索或者进行修修补补时，

他不会自找麻烦，

不会接受那些财产专有权的荒缪概念."


